Distribution: This subspecies is found in Panama , currently known from Chiriquí , Coclé and Panamá provinces. A specimen was recently reported to us which was found in Guanacaste province in the north-west of Costa Rica (
), it was collected whilst flying on the top of Volcán Orosí. The specimen was apparently hilltopping and was caught by hand. This is the northernmost known specimen in the genus, the first record for Costa Rica and a major range extension for the species (
).

